= SDL_SetCursor =
Use this function to set the active cursor.


== Syntax ==
```c++
void SDL_SetCursor(SDL_Cursor* cursor)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''cursor'''
|the SDL_Cursor to apply <<Color2(green,(Should this be linked to Remarks?))>>
|}

== Code Examples ==
*
```c++
int main(int argc, char** argc) {
     SDL_ShowCursor(SDL_DISABLE);
     ...
}
/* creates a blank cursor */
```

== Remarks ==
*<br/>This function sets the currently active cursor to the specified one. If the cursor is currently visible, the change will be immediately represented on the display. [[SDL_SetCursor]](NULL) can be used to force cursor redraw, if this is desired for any reason. <br/>*

